ShopProp is a next-generation real estate platform that combines modern technology with transparent pricing to give buyers and sellers maximum savings and control. Whether you're here to explore our app features, track updates, or integrate with our platform ‚Äî this documentation is your starting point.

üìÖ Release Date: June 20, 2025 üì± Androidv2.0.0üçé iOSv6.1.0 Here's a quick overview of what‚Äôs new in this version: üîê Sign in to unlock features or explore the app in guest mode üó∫Ô∏è Search properties directly on Google Maps with filters and price markers üèòÔ∏è Browse property listings with images and quick access to details üìÑ View complete property details, photos, and take actions like favorite or request ‚ù§Ô∏è Save and view your favorite properties (login required) üé´ Track property requests with filters, notifications, and messages (login required) üí¨ Chat with the team, share documents, and manage tasks with checklists üìù Create a request by selecting location, request type, filling a form, and previewing it before submission

Login & Logout ‚Äì Secure sign-in and sign-out functionality. Guest Mode ‚Äì Explore the app without signing in, with limited access. üîí Note: Some features like saving favorites, creating requests, and accessing conversations are only available when logged in.

Google Map Search ‚Äì Search properties by entering or selecting a location using Google address suggestions. Property Markers ‚Äì Markers on the map display pricing for each listing. Filters ‚Äì Refine your search with filters like: Bedrooms, bathrooms, property type, price range, etc. Saved Filters ‚Äì Save and reuse filter combinations (login required). Marker Interaction ‚Äì Tap a marker to: Preview property details in a popup. Navigate to the full property page by tapping the popup. Favorites ‚Äì Mark/unmark properties as favorites directly from the map (login required).

Card Drawer View ‚Äì Pull up a bottom drawer to view scrollable cards of visible properties. Scroll to Browse ‚Äì Seamless scroll through listings with key property details. Quick Navigation ‚Äì Tap a card to open the property details page. Image Slider ‚Äì Property cards feature horizontal sliders with preview images. Favorite Button ‚Äì Mark any property as a favorite from the card itself (requires login).

Full Property Information ‚Äì Displays address, price, features, and other details. Image Gallery ‚Äì Full-width image slider for immersive property viewing. Request Button ‚Äì Users can express interest or schedule a visit via request. Q&A Shortcut ‚Äì Direct option to start a Q&A conversation from this page. Favorite Toggle ‚Äì Easily mark or unmark property as a favorite (login required).
Saved Properties List ‚Äì View and manage all your marked properties. üîí Requires login to access and sync your favorite listings.

View Requests ‚Äì Users can see all property-related requests (tickets) they‚Äôve created. Quick Filters ‚Äì Toggle between "All", "Active", and "Waiting" tickets. Advanced Filter Options ‚Äì Filter by request type, address, ticket ID, and more. Real-Time Notification Indicator ‚Äì See if a new message has been received. Create Request Button ‚Äì Quickly start a new ticket from this page. Conversation Navigation ‚Äì Tap a ticket to open its associated conversation. üîí Only visible to logged-in users.

Messaging Interface ‚Äì View and respond to ticket-based conversations. Intuitive Layout ‚Äì Clean design with clear separation of message threads. Attachment Support ‚Äì Send pre-uploaded documents in your messages. Type Switcher ‚Äì Switch between different conversation categories (e.g., request, general). ‚úÖ Checklist Integration: Access and interact with a checklist inside the conversation view. Mark items complete or filter to show only unmarked items. üÜï Checklist-to-Chat Shortcut ‚Äì Instantly turn any checklist item into a question or message. üîí Login Required ‚Äì Accessible only for logged-in users.

Google Address Input ‚Äì Type or select property address using Google autocomplete. Request Type Selection ‚Äì Choose the type of inquiry/request. Smart Form Display ‚Äì Auto-loads a relevant form based on request type. Confirmation Step ‚Äì Review all inputs before submission with a confirmation screen. Price Preview ‚Äì Shows a hint price when a Google-selected address is chosen. üîí Login Required ‚Äì Request creation is only available to logged-in users.

Docusaurus blogging features are powered by the blog plugin. Here are a few tips you might find useful. Simply add Markdown files (or folders) to the blog directory. Regular blog authors can be added to authors.yml. The blog post date can be extracted from filenames, such as: 2019-05-30-welcome.md 2019-05-30-welcome/index.md A blog post folder can be convenient to co-locate blog post images: The blog supports tags as well! And if you don't want a blog: just delete this directory, and use blog: false in your Docusaurus config.

üìÖ Release Date: August 01, 2025 üì± Androidv2.2.0üçé iOSv7.2.0 Here's a quick overview of what‚Äôs new in this version: üí∞ Introduced ShopProp Rebate section in the property overview to highlight user savings. üÜï Revamped property details page with new structure, map integration, and rebate visibility. üñºÔ∏è Enhanced image swiper and new full-screen view for property images. üé• Support for 3D virtual tours for immersive property experiences. üìç Map view shows location, with Nearby Homes button for localized listings. üìç Map view shows location inside the property details page. üìä Added new tabs: Zestimate, RPR, WASL Score, and Great Schools. üîê Google sign-in support for seamless onboarding. üè∑Ô∏è Updated fonts, tag styles, and badges for better readability and aesthetics. üêõ Fixed issues with checklist visibility, external links, and scroll behavior. üìç Map now pulls listings using current location and displays accurate counts.

Entire UI/UX redesigned with well-structured sections and tabbed navigation. Added Overview section to quickly show: Key details ShopProp rebate (üí∞) Price per square foot (just below the price) Overview (get Quick overview of the property)
Map now appears in the property details page showing a single pointer for that property. Added "Nearby Homes For Sale" button (top-left of map), leading to nearby listings on the map screen.
Property images are now displayed in a horizontal swiper. Tapping an image opens a full-screen swiper with navigation arrows.
Properties with a 3D tour now show a Virtual Tour button. Tapping opens a full-screen immersive experience.
Properties in Favorites and Listings now display MLS tag below the title. A new Disclaimer section added to Property Details page.
Added new tab for widgets in Property Details: RPR Widget Zestimate WASL Score Great School Ratings
App-wide font styling updated for a more modern and readable design.
Users can now sign in with their Gmail account.
Restyled tags and badges for tickets and property status with consistent color and style.
Fixed bug where multiple templates weren't visible ‚Äî now appear in scrollable vertical sections. External links now render correctly and open in web browser when clicked.
Enhanced performance and fixed inaccurate loading behavior. Property count now correctly shown in cards below the map. Listings now pulled based on user‚Äôs current location.
Improved drag handle interaction in Property Details. Added button behavior to toggle expanded/collapsed state, mimicking drag up/down.

üéØ Save filters without logging in ‚Äì personalize your search with no barriers. üñºÔ∏è Clickable property images ‚Äì tap on images in the property details popup for direct navigation. üìÖ Upgraded DateTime Picker ‚Äì Android gets a custom picker while all platforms support standard forms/requests. üìà Lead tracking ‚Äì capture property visitors, search visitors, and logins for smarter engagement. ‚ö° iOS widget inline loading ‚Äì faster and smoother loading experience. üìê Lot square footage ‚Äì shown only when the data is available. üìù View Form option ‚Äì easily review the full form of a ticket.
Users can now save and re-use filters without requiring an account login. Makes property searching faster and more convenient.
Clicking on property images in the details popup now redirects users to full property details.
A new View Form option lets users easily review the complete form of a ticket. Provides better transparency and improves ticket handling efficiency.
Widgets on iOS now load faster and smoother for a better experience.

ShopProp v4.0 makes your experience even better! üéØ Save filters without logging in, enjoy smarter navigation with clickable property images, and use our new DateTime picker for forms and requests. üìà Lead tracking for property and search visitors is now live. üìù A new View Form option makes reviewing tickets effortless. iOS gets faster widget loading, and property details now show lot square footage only when available. Update now for a smoother, smarter real estate journey!

üìÖ Release Date: July 14, 2025 üì± Androidv2.1.0üçé iOSv7.1.0 Here's a quick overview of what‚Äôs new in this version: üîç Smarter and more reliable property search, with optimized map results, address-based queries, and improved filter handling. üìé Support for document uploads, downloads, and deletions within property attachments. üè° Enhanced property details page to show more relevant information. üìÖ New ability to add open house events to your calendar with a tap. üêû A wide range of bug fixes and UI enhancements for a smoother user experience.

Fixed incorrect map property counts on zoom ‚Äî counts now remain consistent. Map API now gracefully handles out-of-range coordinates. First-time app load (Kirkland) with filters now returns correct property data. Full address search API issues resolved for accurate results. Full address search now includes all statuses (pending, sold, etc.). Property images now load correctly for full address search results. Added missing ‚ÄúPending‚Äù property filter. ‚ÄúSold‚Äù filter now auto-selects ‚ÄúLast 1 Week‚Äù in time range by default. "Sold" quick filter button now highlights using primary theme color. Reopening filter UI after reset now clears previously selected filters. Search returning a single result now redirects to the Property Details page.
Users can now upload, download, and delete documents directly from the property detail page. This helps manage essential files like floor plans, legal documents, and agreements in one place.

The property detail view now includes more comprehensive information, such as amenities, specifications, and additional descriptions. This enhancement ensures better clarity for users exploring property listings.
Users can now add open house events directly to their personal calendar with a single click. This makes it easier to stay organized and never miss scheduled visits.

Ticket replies now correctly mark the ticket as active. Filters on the Tickets page are persisted after refresh. Filter counts now display correctly on the Tickets page. After marking a ticket as done, the tab switches back to ALL (as discussed with Rob). Fixed visibility issue for dynamic form buttons going out of view. Fixed message visibility bug that triggered even on the first load.

Login screen now scrolls properly when the keyboard is open. ‚ÄúAll‚Äù is now the default conversation type in tickets. All modals now close when clicked outside. Improved alignment of additional fields. Updated the "No more tickets to show" message for better clarity. Radio buttons now respond to both the button and label text clicks. Improved dragging experience in the Mode Details section. ‚úÖ Thank you for using ShopProp! We‚Äôre continuously working to improve your experience.
